    "long_instructions": "#### Assessment\r\n\r\nOrganize this song into `intro`, `chorus`, and `verse` functions. The song itself should not change; only how it is organized. When you are finished, you should have 3 functions being called in your program:\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/8569ef83b4f04d7f087838d319aadb43-image-1740586923318.png)\r\n\r\nYou only need to move blocks around in the workspace to solve this level!\r\n\r\nThis is an **Assessment** level, which means it covers the key parts of this lesson. Press the <i class=\"fa-clipboard-list fa-solid\"></i> Rubric button to see what it takes to fully complete this level!\r\n\r\nWhen you've finished the level, press the **Submit** button below! After you submit:\r\n- You won't be able to edit your code! If you need to make a change, you can press Unsubmit to make your edits and then submit again\r\n- Your teacher will be able to give you a score and feedback on your work",
